*Handwritten text:* Diapensiaceae

NORTH CAROLINA FLORA

Species *Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt

Date 27 May 2003                      County Hoke

Location Fort Bragg Military Reservation: north of Manchester Road at Little River Trillium Slopes Natural Area.

Habitat Mesic north-facing slope beside Lower Little River, a blackwater stream. Abundant in narrow zone at crest of river bank under *Kalmia latifolia*, with *Quercus alba*, *Oxydendrum arboreum*, *Ilex opaca*, *Symplocos tinctoria*, *Dichanthelium commutatum*, *Nestronia umbellula*, *Vaccinium tenellum*, *V. elliottii*, *Gaylussacia frondosa*, *Mitchella repens*.

B.A. Sorrie 11066
